`c>>  Philosophy  `f

`lZeroPoint exists because trust should be a protocol
property, not a platform feature.

If your identity lives in a platform's database, your
reputation is computed by a platform's algorithm, and
your authorization chains terminate at a platform's
API -- you do not have trust. You have a lease.

Make trust portable, and you make exit real.
Make exit real, and you make extraction optional.

